H0.text: A hill is indicated by concentric circles on a topographic map.

H1.text: A forest is indicated by concentric circles on a topographic map.

H2.text: A lake is indicated by concentric circles on a topographic map.

H3.text: Concentric circles on a topographic map indicate a crater.

A4.text: The rule of Os: closed loops are normally uphill on the inside and downhill on the outside, and the innermost loop is the highest area.
